<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-023-388  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 023 388.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Jan 6 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>UK: CIX subscribers launch project for charity. (United Kingdom,Compulink Information eXchange)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gold, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer industryCompulink Information eXchange (Information retrieval system)Drake Research FundUnited KingdomDonationInformation Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>UK: CIX SUBSCRIBERS LAUNCH PROJECT FOR CHARITY LONDON, ENGLAND, 1990 JAN 06(NB) -- DJ Walker-Morgan, better known as DJ to online friends and colleagueson the Compulink Information eXchange (CIX) online service, has organized therelease of a tape of musical compositions from fellow CIX subscribers.andM;The tape - Radio CIX - costs UKP 5-00 ($8-00), with all profits going to theDrake Research Fund, a UK charity.andM;The Drake Research Fund is a charity set up by Adele Drake to help disabledchildren communicate via the medium of music.andP;  These kids, who might only beable to move one finger, can been shown how to use synthesizers, drummachines and computer based sequencers, both as a way of learning music andalso as a form of communication.andM;According to DJ, the solutions to the technical problems that face the MIDIinstrument designer can also be applied to the human body.andP;  This isespecially important if the person has very limited movement options.andP;  Neattricks such as gesture control of synthesizers via MIDI could thus become alifeline for someone who is physically disabled.andM;Like any charity, the Drake Research Project always needs money and support.andO;Hence the Radio CIX project.andP;  According to DJ, &quot;Newsbytes readers whopurchase the Radio CIX tape will hear more than forty minutes of good musicrecorded by CIX onliners such as Ahavenhand, Brianh, Poppytime and many more.andO;Not only that, tape buyers will be giving to a good cause, and that can't bebad, can it?&quot;andM;(Steve Gold/19900106/Press Contact: DJ Walker-Morgan - Tel: 01-960-2623;Public Contact: DJ - The Radio Cix Project, 20 Mostyn Gardens, Kensall Rise,London NW10 - Email: DJ on Cix).andO;</TEXT></DOC>